# This file is kept as a placeholder for legacy tooling. QBZ no longer reads
# third-party API credentials from a .env file — Last.fm, Discogs, Tidal,
# Spotify-import, and MusicBrainz all go through the Cloudflare Workers
# proxy at qbz-api-proxy.blitzkriegfc.workers.dev, with the URL hardcoded as
# a const in each service module (src-tauri/src/lastfm/mod.rs,
# discogs/mod.rs, playlist_import/providers/tidal.rs, musicbrainz/client.rs).
#
# Source builds work out of the box without any keys. If you want to use
# your own proxy, deploy https://github.com/vicrodh/qbz-api-proxy and edit
# the *_PROXY_URL constants in the service modules above.
